{
"court": "High Court of Sindh",
"case_type": "",
"year": "2016",
"legal_issue": "The instant petition alongwith connected petition was disposed of vide common order dated 03.10.2017 with following observations:- \n\"Counsels have agreed that respondent No.4 should not act as a Secretary of the Society until and unless the appeal pending before Secretary Cooperative Society would be decided; if in case, such appeal is not pending, the parties may prefer an appeal including the clients of Mr. Muhammad Arshad S. Pathan advocate to raise questions regarding the authority to review and revisit the order by the Registrar in terms of order dated 30.06.2014. The Secretary shall decide the appeal or any other application i.e.\npreferred by the parties and the question as raised by the counsel as to the entitlement of being a member of the society or otherwise within four weeks, after hearing all the parties concerned. This order decides the fate of respondent No.4 as to whether he still is a\nmember or otherwise. However he for all intent and purposes cease\nto be Secretary of Society. Without prejudice to above decision, two members committee consisting of Additional Registrar of this Court and Mr. Anwarul Haq son of Khan Bahadur Abdul Aziz bearing CNIC No.41304-4646382-3 is constituted who shall act upon the\nrecommendations of the enquiry officer and shall also monitor the day to day expenses. Respondent No.4 cease to operate as secretary of the Society and that orders be sent to the concerned Bank Manager that the bank account of the Society shall not be operated by respondent No.4 and shall only be operated by two members of the committee referred above. The two members shall\n--- PAGE ---\nC.P. No.D-384 of 2016\nresume the charge of the office of the Secretary within two days from today and if possible the charge be resumed today. The committee shall formulate the list of the members within three weeks. The entire process including election may not take more than 10 weeks in all. Periodical compliance report be filed by the Additional Registrar fortnightly. The fee of Supervisory Committee is fixed at Rs.40,000/- to be paid from Society’s account.\nBoth these petitions in the above terms stand disposed of.\"",
"keywords": ["Contempt of Court Ordinance", "Section 3 & 4", "Article 204"]
}

